 \\]", "6": "Adding up all the squares, we get: \\[ 16 + 9 + 4 + 1 = 30 \\]", "7": "The fraction of rectangles that are squares is: \\[ \\frac{\\text{Number of squares}}{\\text{Total number of rectangles}} = \\frac{30}{100} = \\frac{3}{10} \\] Thus, the fraction of the rectangles in set \\( R \\) that are squares is: \\[ \\boxed{\\frac{3}{10}} \\]"}

