 + \\sqrt{3}\\]", "3": "Finally, we calculate the shaded area. The area of the shaded region is the area of the large semicircle minus the unshaded area calculated in the previous step: \\[A_{\\text{shaded}} = A_{\\text{large semicircle}} - A_{\\text{unshaded}} = 2\\pi - \\left(\\frac{3}{2}\\pi + \\sqrt{3}\\right) = 2\\pi - \\frac{3}{2}\\pi - \\sqrt{3}\\] Simplifying this expression gives: \\[A_{\\text{shaded}} = \\frac{1}{2}\\pi - \\sqrt{3}\\] Therefore, the area of the shaded region, expressed in simplest radical form and in terms of \\(\\pi\\), is: \\[ \\boxed{\\frac{1}{2}\\pi - \\sqrt{3}} \\]"}

